form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Part 12. Additional Information About You (Person Applying for Naturalization) (continued), Form N-400

full_text: Screened by NARA, 9/26/2023 2018093921220 2932802 CODES 62 w526838 042718 Part 12. Additional Information About You (Person Applying for A- 4 2 4 5 1 2 Naturalization) (continued) Answer Item Numbers 30. - 46. If you answer "Yes" to any of these questions, except Item Numbers 37. and 38., include a typed or printed explanation on additional sheets of paper and provide any evidence to support your answers. 30. Have you EVER: A. Been a habitual drunkard? Yes x NB B. Been a prostitute, or procured anyone for prostitution? Yes x N6 C. Sold or smuggled controlled substances, illegal drugs, or narcotics? Yes x No D. Been married to more than one person at the same time? Yes x No E. Married someone in order to obtain an immigration benefit? Yes x No F. Helped anyone to enter, or try to enter, the United States illegally? Yes x No G. Gambled illegally or received income from illegal gambling? Yes x No H. Failed to support your dependents or to pay alimony? Yes x No I. Made any misrepresentation to obtain any public benefit in the United States? Yes x No 31. Have you EVER given any U.S. Government officials any information or documentation that was false, Yes x No fraudulent, or misleading? 32. Have you EVER lied to any U.S. Government officials to gain entry or admission into the United States or Yes x No to gain immigration benefits while in the United States? 33. Have you EVER been removed, excluded, or deported from the United States? Yes x No 34. Have you EVER been ordered removed, excluded, or deported from the United States? Yes X No 35. Have you EVER been placed in removal, exclusion, rescission, or deportation proceedings? Yes x No 36. Are removal, exclusion, rescission, or deportation proceedings (including administratively closed Yes x No proceedings) currently pending against you? 37. Have you EVER served in the U.S. armed forces? Yes x No 38. A. Are you currently a member of the U.S. armed forces? Yes x No B. If you answered "Yes," are you scheduled to deploy overseas, including to a vessel, within the next Yes X No three months? (Refer to the Address Change section in the Instructions on how to notify USCIS if you learn of your deployment plans after you file your Form N-400.) C. If you answered "Yes," are you currently stationed overseas? Yes x No 39. Have you EVER been court-martialed, administratively separated, or disciplined, or have you received an Yes x No other than honorable discharge, while in the U.S. armed forces? 40. Have you EVER been discharged from training or service in the U.S. armed forces because you were an Yes X No alien? 41. Have you EVER left the United States to avoid being drafted in the U.S. armed forces? Yes x No 42. Have you EVER applied for any kind of exemption from military service in the U.S. armed forces? Yes X No 43. Have you EVER deserted from the U.S. armed forces? Yes X No Form N-400 03/26/16 N Page 15 of 20
